{WEST has a nice 2\C opening hand.

With 8 points, EAST can make a positive response so he bids his 5-card \Hsuit.

WEST likes \Hs, knows there are at least 33 points, but needs to make 
sure the opponents don't have two Aces so she uses Blackwood.

When EAST shows one Ace WEST bids 6\H.}

